The following is  a part of the Organization Rest API.  

"GET /admin/v1/orgs/\{orgId}/users", you'll see the following and in this response there is only a single reference to the email address.
{code:java}
{
"account_id":"xxxx",
"account_type":"atlassian",
"account_status":"Active",
"name":"xxxx",
"picture":"",
"email":"xxxxx",
"access_billable":true,
"product_access":[{"siteUrl":"xxxx","productName":"xxxxx","productKey":"xxxxx"}],
"links":{"self":"https://api.atlassian.com/users/xxxORGIDxxxx/manage/profile"}
}{code}
UPN is not available in the above and some organisations need this for control of organisations and organisational reporting.

h3. Issue Summary

As per [The User provisioning REST API - Retrieve users from a directory|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/admin/user-provisioning/rest/#api-scim-directory-directoryId-Users-get] the /scim/directory/\{directoryId\}/Users endpoint should be hit with:
{noformat:bgColor=#f8f8f8}
curl --request GET \
--url 'https://api.atlassian.com/scim/directory/\{directoryId}/Users' \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer <access_token>' \
--header 'Accept: application/json'
{noformat}

But doing a call with those headers results in:
{noformat:bgColor=#f8f8f8}
{"timestamp":"2019-xx-xxTxx:xx:xx.xxx+0000","status":406,"error":"Not Acceptable","message":"Not Acceptable","path":"/api/scim/directory/{directoryId}/Users"}
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results

The endpoint should successfully return the list of users in a JSON format.

h3. Workaround

Remove the *Accept: application/json* header from the call or replace it with *Accept: application/scim+json*.

